# Cursor Rules — sqlserver_copilot_forex

## Project
Forex ML training pipeline. Multi-model ensemble for Buy/Sell/Hold predictions on 10 currency pairs.

## Stack
- Python 3.11+, XGBoost, LightGBM, scikit-learn, pandas, numpy, pyodbc
- SQL Server (192.168.86.55\MSSQLSERVER01, stockdata_db, SQL Auth)

## Architecture
- feature_engineering.py → 100+ features from OHLCV data
- ensemble_builder.py → XGBoost, LightGBM, Voting, Stacking models
- predict_daily.py → Daily predictions → forex_ml_predictions table
- 3-class classification (Buy/Sell/Hold) — NOT binary
- Forex prices are DECIMAL (not VARCHAR like equity tables)

## Output Table
- forex_ml_predictions (currency_pair, date, signal, confidence, probabilities, model_name, model_version)

## 10 Currency Pairs
USD/INR, EUR/USD, GBP/USD, USD/JPY, AUD/USD, USD/CAD, NZD/USD, EUR/GBP, EUR/JPY, GBP/JPY

## Schedule
- 7:00 AM daily predictions
- Sunday 6:00 AM weekly retrain

## Ecosystem
Part of 7-repo trading platform. Predictions consumed by stockdata_agenticai (Forex Agent) and streamlit-trading-dashboard.
- sqlserver_mcp — .NET 8 MCP Server (Microsoft MssqlMcp): 7 tools (ListTables, DescribeTable, ReadData, CreateTable, DropTable, InsertData, UpdateData) via stdio. Use to explore DB schemas/data during development.

